This weekend was the 1st and LAST time I will ever take my 3 children to BAB!¬† I was one of the, I'm sure many, disappointed parents that wanted to take their children to your Pay your age event on July 12th.¬† I have 3 children under the age of 6 so when I heard of your event and it was going to be on my daughter's 4th Birthday I thought to myself we can't miss this!¬† After hearing about the mayhem and that you would be sending out coupons for $15 off I thought this just might work out for us since like I mentioned we have 3 kids so your bears are not the most larger family reasonable to purchase.¬† Which brings us to today......

I took my 3 very excited kids to get their 1st BAB!¬† When checking out I was told that the coupon is good for only 1 bear.¬† I asked the girl at the counter if the promotion was for only 1 kid or was it for every kid per family.¬† She said that yes it was for every kid in the family.¬† So then I asked why then is the coupon for only 1 child and she did not know.¬† I asked to speak to her manager and she just laughed and very rude and condescending said call the number on your receipt.¬† Wow!¬† That's all!¬† I was very surprised by her lack of remorse or even just good old fashion customer service skills.¬† I made sure to get her name Sofia in the Ontario Mills BAB and she just glared at me as if to shoot daggers at me.¬† Again what happened to the old fashioned customer service... my small children were in there with me so I left it alone and just left the store.

I ended up having what started out as a very exciting family adventure to leaving with fumes coming out and sitting in the car ride the entire time typing this email!

Signed a VERY DISSATISFIED DISAPPOINTED FURIOUS CUSTOMER NO MORE!</review>

<userid>104391725146946372378</userid>< user_name>
Julie Healon<//user_name>
< Date>
1500566336728</Date>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< review>
This was so fun! We were just strolling by, on the way to Dave and Busters. Decided to pop in, and check it out. I had heard they have Star Trek bears. We looked around, and nothing.

On our way out, my hubby asked if they have ever seen a Star Trek one here. She says yes! And takes him to a bin. Where one lone Spok bear was hiding. Then, took us to a shelf, and in the far back, there were outfits for them. Yes!

So, we got him. It was super busy there. We were 7th in line to fill our bear. But it moves super quick. You then pick a sound, (optional at an additional charge) and  then get your bear stuffed.  You hold the petal down with your foot, while the person working does the stuffing.

They have a ritual, which, being adults, she may have sensed our hesitancy, and made it simple. You put a heart on your nose, make a wish, kiss the heart, and it goes inside the bear. Super cute. It may be more elaborate for kids.

They have a station with a brush, to clean him up, and dress. We just took ours home. Then, a station to make, and print a birth certificate. Very adorable, but we opted out of that. We got the bear, with sound, 1 outfit, and a phaser. Came out to about 52 dollars. More than we expected. But worth it.

It was a fun experience. Staff was super friendly, and helpful. Make sure to ask, if you don't see something you are looking for! They have SO many options!< /review>

< Text>
I have never visited a chiropractor before out of fear that it will make my neck and back pain worse let alone the The horrifying sound of popping. Dealing with chronic pain is life changing and depressing. Everyday I deal with pain and extremely painful numb arms, hands and fingers. Today I had my first appointment and I'm so thankful I took the plunge and faced my fears. I received an adjustment and massage. As soon as both were done I felt different not different that all my pain magically disappeared but my pain changed, my numbness is still here but it isn't the burning stabbing numbness it's more of a numbness like a foot going to sleep (so much better) but what has changed most just after 1 appointment is my mindset. The pain CAN be treated and I have hope and determination now where as this morning and any other day lately I didn't care if I lived or died. Having the massage after was really something great and he worked out a couple issues that I didn't even know existed. Over all I'm thankful and will be spending time with living roots. I would recommend this place for anyone needing healing.<//Text>

< Review>
A friend had been going here was a while, and I had heard nothing but good things from her about her experience. She ended up finding me a Groupon deal there for a chiropractic adjustment and 3 massages for under $100 (great deal by the way). And with nagging muscle and alignment issues, how could I say no? The office is small and quaint up front, but opens up in the back to several chiropractic and massage areas. Dr. Lily was very professional and social, which was a plus, and she did an excellent job. The deep tissue massage was great as well, and was needed just as much as the alignment. I look for forward to the 2 more as part of my package deal. A helpful piece of advice prior to your massage is to make sure you're properly hydrated before and after.

I was and it made muscle fatigue and soreness nonexistent for me. I'll definitely be going back in the future for my chiropractic issues and massage needs, and highly recommend their services< /Review>

All employees and residents wear masks (thankfully) and the building has enough shared space for residents to comfortably social distance in an amenity section. Did I mention how beautiful the indoor building decor is? As well as little details in my apartment?! I am so pleased with the clean design that's still homey, modern, spacious, and welcoming.

<Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMuw9Bg-RaWa76JSxkLEHdU8VxrGTcjqfMuH3i8=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics><Text>We just received our custom-built 1500 horsepower MMR 5.3 liter long block built for our 2003 Mercury Marauder. This vendor is the real deal, will deliver what they promise you, and is a joy to work with.
We ordered the custom-built motor from MMR via Greg, who went out of the way to answer all our technical questions from the beginning.  We told him our requirements (up to 30 psi boost from a 4L Whipple with a later option to add NOS). Greg suggested ported and polished heads and a stage 2 Comp cams. He clearly explained technically his reasoning for the addition of the extras and the gains we will get from the same, he is clearly a race expert. We agreed to the build, the final price and actually added some more extras at our own choice, including a high-volume oil pump with billet gears, billet crank position wheel and red fire- coated pistons.  The timeframe for the build was clearly defined at the outset.
During the build, we had questions and called him often. Greg always came to the phone and went out of his way to answer our technical questions. We wish we could say that for all other vendors in the US, but unfortunately some other vendors are hard to get a hold of and will not answer emails. Not MMR - we always had phone and email responses from them and Greg should take the credit for that.  Greg was patient with us as we requested ETA updates towards the end of our build period.
The motor arrived on a pallet, well-mounted and protected from any possible damage. Since it was International shipping to Canada, we also requested that we ship with another company instead of their regular shipper. Greg had no problem with that and accommodated us without issues. The motor is a work of art and the quality that Greg put into it is hard to duplicate.
As we started to bolt on the components, we noticed that the block had missing dowel pins. Not MMR‚Äôs fault, the block came from Ford Racing and I guess they just don‚Äôt add the dowel pins to the block. We called Greg at MMR and he shipped us a dowel kit and didn‚Äôt even charge us for them.
We would highly recommend using MMR for any custom-built motors/products!  The quality and customer service are hard to beat.  And we did contact several other builders before choosing MMR and can confirm MMR‚Äôs pricing to be competitive in the marketplace.< /Text><Date>1604956009852< /Date><resp>None<//resp>< name>

< review>
Well it started off a little rocky. If anyone read my review before this, I was a little heated and short tempered.
I‚Äôm editing this review now because In the end, things got ironed out.
I know these guys are trying to run a company along with run a race team. Juggling business on two fronts.
I didn‚Äôt get the cams I wanted but the ones I got seem to be fine. I‚Äôm not sure if the step up would have made a huge difference other than the sound at idle.
There was some mix up with cam cap bolts, I ended up fixing that myself even though I had to pay another store, so basically charged twice for the same thing.
A few more small parts were over looked but everything worked out in the end.
As for the build of the block, we are in the process of tuning right now and everything seems to be holding up.
Their oil cooler system for the GT500 is pretty damn awesome. My engine temps are down by almost 20 degrees. We have great oil pressure with their hurricane pump. The engine is balanced damn near perfectly. The car never ran this smooth when it was new.
The power output on the same boost as when it was stock is pretty amazing.

I am very satisfied with the build of the short block itself.
I wish I would have gotten the correct cams and other parts. I did have to jump through some hoops to get this thing back together.

There may have been some misconception about the cams on their website. Maybe a better description of what they consider the cams to be. On all other websites, the stage 2 comp cam is what MMR considers a stage 3. So when I thought I was getting a stage 3, it was actually a stage 2.

Now that this thing is up and running, time will tell on how much abuse this thing can take. We are at 15psi now. We will be cranking it up in a few weeks on race gas and see what this little mod motor can do.<//review>

<user_id>111966813957691982635<//user_id><name>matt wojdy<//name><Date>1462658407336</Date><rating>1< /rating><text>I ordered a stroker kit, and received it just fine.  Unfortunately, they sent me a set of completely mismatched pistons and my kit was missing parts.  They were from three or four different batches, and there was a ten gram difference between the lightest and heaviest of each.  Manley piston sets are very rarely comprised of pistons from multiple batches, and are "set matched" to ensure they are within three grams of each other.   I contacted MMR over the phone, and whoever answered did not find that to be an issue in our initial conversation, and told me to have my machinist cut some material off.  I told him I wanted a matched set, just like Manley would have sent them, so the fellow at MMR said he'd "look into it."  A few days go by without response so I call again, and email.  At this point, they told me to send in the pistons "to inspect, and if there are any issues, they will replace them for me."  The issue was clear.  Before sending them, I asked them to email a paid shipping label since this was an issue on THEIR end.  I was told their system wasn't set up that way, but they would reimburse me in full for the cost of shipping the pistons if they were "found to be bad."  Well they were bad. At this point a few weeks had gone by, two or three, then another one or two weeks to get a set of matched pistons.  Then, they refused to reimburse me for the shipping cost, and Greg said he, "would never say something like that," referencing reimbursing me for the shipping costs.  His actual words.  In the end I did get a reimbursement, but it was almost six months later, after disputing it with the credit card company, and getting them on our side.

Moral of the story, I'd never go back, and never recommend them.  They don't quality control before shipment.  Take their BBB rating with a grain of salt.  They are not a BBB accredited company and literally have ONE review on there, giving MMR the A rating they reference in the other complaints.

Though the customer service experience was more of a 3, the coffee was so great I‚Äôm still leaving 5 stars. They mixed up several orders, including mine, and things got a bit chaotic for a bit. The baristas were visibly flustered, but things happen. As far as the coffee, the roast is just right, they know how to pull proper espresso shots (even decaf), the cream is fresh and local, and they keep the sweetness at just the right amount to let the espresso shine through. If you‚Äôre looking for a great quality coffee or espresso, I would highly recommend.< /text>

<rating>5< /rating>< text>
Visited family for the weekend and my uncle took us here during the local farmer's market. Lot of amazing food and nice people! There was also vendors selling a range of goods and it was interesting to see various types of art that I'm not used to. Would definitely check it out if you love fresh produce and supporting local vendors! I believe the farmers market is only on the weekends but I'd double check before heading there.</text>

<Gmap_id>0x808f8743e241fd7f:0x41a6fce50dea69c7< /Gmap_id>< text>
A gem of an urban park, mostly maintained by neighborhood volunteers. The Saturday farmer's market is year-round, and well worth a visit. Restaurants in the Grand Lake neighborhood (on Grand and Lakeshore) are diverse and welcoming. The Grand Lake Theatre shows first run movies and include an organ player on Friday and Saturday evenings. A walk around Lake Merritt is a 3 mile jaunt well worth the effort.</text>

Honestly, I can't say enough good things about this place. My vehicle had major damage after an accident and I just assumed it was never going to be the same again. What made it even worse was that it was still fairly new. I ended up taking it to a few different places for estimates and that's how I found this place. The sales manager Shane Keheian immediately made me feel confident that they could handle the job and they went above and beyond my high expectations. Shane handled everything with my insurance adjuster, all I had to do was hand him the key. Fast forward four months later, I had a minor issue that was totally unrelated to any repairs they had done and I called Shane. He told me to bring the car in and a few hours later he called me and told me they fixed it free of charge. Not many places go above and beyond but this place certainly does. If you've ever been in an accident or need work done, I highly recommend this place. Ask for Shane Keheian, you'll be happy you did.</text>

< Text>
Are there dozens of body shops near that you could choose? Yes. Will they fix your car? Yes. Will it be done well and on time? Who knows? Will they treat you like their only customer? Like a member of the family? Probably not... but that‚Äôs what Fountain Valley Bodyworks does.

It takes a lot for me to bother with a review but‚Ä¶I‚Äôve been to FV Bodyworks 4 times (don‚Äôt judge me-only once was my fault). The first time was on a friend‚Äôs referral, but I keep coming back because it‚Äôs the only place I will choose for bodywork on my cars.

It seems almost impossible to find quality customer service not to mention expert craftsmanship but FV Bodyworks does just that. I can only explain it by observing that it‚Äôs a culture that manager Mike Honrath encourages.

My last visit was on 7-1-20 and, unlike the other times, I didn‚Äôt leave my car overnight. I just needed a new bumper, so I went down and paid for a bumper and set an appointment for a replacement. When I returned, I waited for the new bumper to be attached. While I was sitting and reading, I was astounded by all the customers who came in for a variety of reasons and were all treated as excellently as I had become accustomed to. A flurry of activity with extra sanitizing due to Covid going on with employees working hard at their jobs but always kind and professional to customers and each other. Employees who had no need to interact with me still smiled, said hello and offered assistance.

Knowledgeable, expert, on time, willing to go the extra mile and make anything right, clean finished product, on time AND will treat you with respect and dignity. What a great place! I hope I never have to go back but, if the need arises, I will return ONLY to FV Bodyworks.</Text>

excellent care of me.  I understand why your shop is voted the best bodyshop in Orange County.  I will never go anywhere else for my vehicle repair needs.  I highly recommend this company for any vehicle that is in need of body work.

I've rated Fountain Valley Bodyworks five stars because they excel in all areas of business.  Knowledgeable and friendly customer service, exceptional and rapid repair work and more than reasonable pricing.

I pulled in on a Friday evening for a price quote.  I made an appointment that was convenient for me.  I was in and out of there in 10 minutes.
I returned on Wednesday morning and Horacio remembered what I was there for.  Originally I was told the repair would take approximately 2 hours; and, to my surprise, Horacio had my car repaired in 30 minutes.  An even bigger surprise was that, even though I was super happy with the original quote to repair, I was charged even less than the original quote!!!

Horacio surprised me by taking it upon himself to buff out and paint the scratches at no charge.  My car looks brand new again and I could not be happier. The two girls at the desk were a complete pleasure to work with on both Friday and Wednesday.  Michael, the owner, made sure that I was completely satisfied with the work as I was paying my bill.  Horacio walked me to my car as I was leaving.

BEWARE: They do not stand by their lifetime warranty/work.

I had my car repaired here almost a year and a half ago and they did what I thought was a phenomenal job. However, as time went on, I noticed paint chipping off from where they did their repair. Today, I brought my car back to the shop and was expecting them to fix it for me due to their lifetime warranty. HOWEVER, they gave me the run around and told me that the size of my rims caused the paint damage, and that they would not repair the paint chipping under their lifetime warranty. I went and compared the repaired side to the other side of the car (the side with no repairs needed) and found that there were no paint chipping off on that side. Shocking. This led me to think, ‚ÄúWhy is the paint on the repaired side coming off, and the nonrepaired side is totally fine?‚Äù If the rims are the problem, both sides should be having the same issues, but no‚Ä¶only the side that‚Äôs been repaired is having the paint chipping issues.

I am extremely disappointed. Fountain Valley Body Works was my go-to place for any type of car repairs, but after this experience, never again. I will no longer refer any of my friends or family to this body shop.<//review>

<user>114994951398291854035< /user><user_name>Solitude Heisenberg<//user_name>< date>

<rate>5< /rate><Text>I've been to this shop a couple times over the years, but before there was any kind of social media to review businesses like this.  So when someone damaged my left-rear door, this was the only place I seriously considered.

I now live over an hour away, so I looked at shops in my area first.  However, I was really concerned about the quality of the repairs and the painter's ability to match the color (3-stage, pearl white).  Based on my memory of past experiences with Fountain Valley Bodyworks, I was hoping my drive would still be worth it, and I'm glad I made that call.

I had an idea to repair (not replace) the door, to save me from blending the adjacent quarter panel.  Mike Honrath took his time and rationally discussed the repairs with me, and I'm really glad he did.  What we ended up doing, replacing the door, was a far better "repair" than what I was previously considering.  I didn't want to blend the adjacent quarter panel or do anything to the factory paint, but Mike convinced me that it was the better repair and he was right.

Based on Mr. Honrath's suggestion, I was also able to save a little money when calling Enterprise Rent-A-Car (located right down the street) by mentioning that I was getting my car repaired at FV Bodyworks.  It couldn't have worked out any better than it did.

FV Bodyworks staff was friendly, and made the whole process great (considering it was an already bad situation of having to fix my car).  Mike Honrath, particularly, really ended up making me feel comfortable with everything that was needed and done to my car.

I've been to other body shops before going here the first time.  There is a reason why they are voted the #1 Body Shop in all of Orange County for five years in a row; and there is a reason why a person like Mike Honrath is in the position he is, and has worked there for as long as he has.  If I ever need additional work on my car, I will be going here again.

Thank you FV Bodyworks, and THANK YOU Mike!</Text>< Pics>

< Review>
I was very pleased with the customer service and repairs from Fountain Valley Body Works.  I was rear ended in my 2011 Hyndai Elantra and State Farms Insurance recommended that I take my car there.  The estimator was extremely helpful and told me about their $350 bumper special.  They were able to fix the bumper quickly and the paint job was spot on!  I really couldn't tell at all that damage had been done to my car when I picked it up.  The workers were friendly, professional, and proactive about fixing my car on time (I didn't have to call to ask if my car was done yet, like I've had to do at other body shops in the past).  I highly recommend FVBW Express and I'll definitely take a car back there if I need to (fingers crossed for no more fender benders!).< /Review>

<Rate>5< /Rate><Text>Suki Time Thai Kitchen is me and my wife's favorite Thai restaurant (and restaurant in general). We come here fairly often (every few weeks or so) and order something new during each visit. The main favorite item to order is their Thai coconut coffee - it is far more flavorful and delicious than any coffee franchise, and comes in a very large bottle. All in all, every meal we have ordered has never disappointed, and the staff are all incredibly sweet, attentive, and helpful. We never feel rushed out of the restaurant when we are near the end of our meals, and the prices are also more than reasonable. This place will always be one of our fondest memories shared in Lomita. < Review>
First time visiting a "Del Taco" and was impressed. Very similar to "Taco Bell" but with several burgers available on the menu. Fast friendly drive thru with a perfectly filled order. Dollar menu is great!! Easy to navigate location.
Full family approval! Kids enjoyed the burgers and fries while the wife and I enjoyed tacos nachos and chips.
I would rank slightly better than "Taco Bell".. "Del Taco" had more of a "fresh" taste in my opinion and a less expensive alternative.
Will definately return again soon!!</Review>

<time>1521730486602</time>< Rating>
3< /Rating>
< text>
Food itself was eadible and we didn't get sick from it, so I suppose that's good. However, it was very greasy (moreso than other taquerias), bland and lacked complexity in it's flavor. Better than other fast food taco chains, but still a fast food taco chain, so don't expect much. It was the only place around to grab something quick out our way to Tahoe and went in with low expectations (the place being a fast food chain and all), so we weren't disappointed. You get what you pay for... "Authentic" Mexican food it isn't, but it's fast, cheap and clean. Oh, no public restroom there.<//text>
